{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure mode is usually at a module boundary: diff parsing plus prompt/input assembly. A unit test of only the formatter can miss leaks from upstream diff selection logic.","test_description":"Run the reviewer against a synthetic repo change where unchanged sections contain obvious lint/bug bait text; assert the constructed review payload contains only added/modified hunks and excludes untouched file regions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Position mapping failures often appear only against the real PR diff API semantics (line/side/commit anchoring). Mocks can accept invalid mappings and hide production failures.","test_description":"Create a real test PR with known changed lines, post inline comments through the automation, then fetch PR review comments from GitHub and verify each comment anchors to the intended file/hunk/line in the live diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model judgment over code quality. Deterministic mocks cannot validate true defect-detection capability or nondeterministic model behavior.","test_description":"Use a PR fixture containing a seeded real bug (for example, swallowed exception or off-by-one), run the real model reviewer repeatedly under fixed prompt/tooling, and assert at least one run flags the seeded defect with actionable evidence.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a consistency invariant across internal finding aggregation and comment-post result handling. It is mainly cross-module state/wiring, not OS/network behavior by itself.","test_description":"Run end-to-end logic with a controllable PR-comment client stub that returns posted inline comment IDs; assert summary entries are generated only from successfully posted inline findings and each summary item references an existing inline artifact.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment — completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a full agent pipeline across sequential stages and external side effects, typically including at least one real agentic review step plus downstream posting actions.","test_description":"Trigger the automation on a real GitHub test PR and let it run unattended; verify pipeline completion status, presence of inline comments, and presence of a top-level summary comment that reflects produced findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.24,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.55}}]}
